About Me

I'm Kushagra, a passionate web designer and developer based in Bhopal. I specialize in building clean, functional websites that deliver great user experiences. I’m also an internationally rated chess player and the founder of Unicorn Chess Academy, where I teach strategy and game analysis.

Study

I am currently pursuing a Bachelor's degree in Computer Science with specialization of AI & ML at Jagran Lakecity University. My coursework focuses on web development, database systems, data structures, and software engineering. I actively participate in coding competitions, technical fests, and workshops to expand my knowledge beyond the classroom.

At university, I’ve built several academic projects including responsive websites, mini web applications, and database-driven tools using modern frameworks. I am especially passionate about front-end development and enjoy blending design with functionality.

Sports

I am an internationally rated chess player with an official FIDE ELO rating of 1832. Over the years, I have participated in numerous national and international chess tournaments. My journey in chess has not only sharpened my strategic thinking but also taught me the value of discipline, focus, and resilience under pressure.

My dedication to the sport has been recognized multiple times, most notably by JLU University, where I was honored with the "Outstanding Achievement in Sports" award during the annual Foundation Day celebration. Chess continues to be a significant part of my life, and I am passionate about promoting the game through mentorship and training young talents.
